2
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:46,625
I can't believe that
this hot bath feels so good.

3
00:01:46,708 --> 00:01:47,958
It's like heaven.

4
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,375
[Mugen] Just sayin'.

5
00:01:49,458 --> 00:01:51,500
Don't you think
it's a little bit fishy?

6
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:52,833
How do you mean?

7
00:01:52,916 --> 00:01:54,958
Like, what the hell
are we wanderin' around for?

8
00:01:55,041 --> 00:01:56,333
We're searching for

9
00:01:56,416 --> 00:01:58,375
the samurai who smells
of sunflowers, as I recall.

10
00:01:58,458 --> 00:01:59,750
That's exactly what I'm sayin'.

11
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:01,500
I mean, if you stop
and think about it,

12
00:02:01,583 --> 00:02:02,750
we really don't know jack shit

13
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,916
about this
sunflower dude, do we?

14
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,875
That's true.

15
00:02:05,958 --> 00:02:08,041
Yeah, remember that one time?

16
00:02:08,125 --> 00:02:09,625
[tape rewinding]

17
00:02:09,708 --> 00:02:12,541
Oh yeah, the smelly guy, I been
meanin' to ask you about that.

18
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:13,833
Huh?

19
00:02:13,916 --> 00:02:15,416
Who is this samurai
who smells of sunflowers?

20
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,500
Well, he...

21
00:02:16,583 --> 00:02:18,500
What the hell
is a sunflower anyway?

22
00:02:18,583 --> 00:02:19,291
Wait a minute-

23
00:02:19,375 --> 00:02:20,291
You don't know?

24
00:02:20,375 --> 00:02:21,458
It's a flower.

25
00:02:21,541 --> 00:02:22,500
So what do they smell like?

26
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:23,875
You have any other leads?

27
00:02:23,958 --> 00:02:25,125
Like a picture
or somethin'?

28
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:26,416
What makes you think
he's around here?

29
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,541
Aah! Stop!

30
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:29,916
You ever notice
she gets all weasely

31
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,041
when we bring that stuff up?

32
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:33,250
Mmm.

33
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,125
And this latest shit,
now she expects us

34
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:37,416
to go all the way to Nagasaki.

35
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:38,666
[tape rewinding]

36
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:40,708
[Jouji] I'm sorry,
but there's only one thing

37
00:02:40,791 --> 00:02:42,041
that I can tell you:

38
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:44,166
Nagasaki is where
you should to look.

39
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:47,208
I am sure you might be able
to find answers there.

40
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:49,208
Nagasaki.

41
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:51,166
So we're just supposed
to believe this idiot

42
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:52,625
and go all the way there?

43
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:54,750
[Jin] Still, the man was
the chief merchant

44
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:57,083
of the East India Company's
Japan branch.

45
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:59,500
I doubt his information
would be unreliable.

46
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:00,375
Are you sure?

47
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:01,708
What's the difference?

48
00:03:01,791 --> 00:03:04,166
With no other leads,
we haven't got much choice.

49
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,875
That's exactly what I'm sayin'.

50
00:03:05,958 --> 00:03:07,708
There's no way in hell
she doesn't know more

51
00:03:07,791 --> 00:03:09,458
than she's lettin' on.

52
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:12,041
That little tramp
is hiding somethin' from us.

53
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:13,208
Mmm.

54
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:14,916
[Mugen] Okay then.

55
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,500
What are you doing?

56
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:19,541
While she's busy takin' a bath,
I'm gonna snoop around a little.

57
00:03:19,625 --> 00:03:30,041
[Fuu humming]

58
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:31,541
[Mugen] Here we go.

59
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,333
[Jin] You shouldn't go through
other people's belongings.

60
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:35,166
Hey, chill out, will ya?

61
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:37,833
It's her own fault
for not tellin' us anything.

62
00:03:40,166 --> 00:03:41,666
[Jin] What is it?

63
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,958
I can't read.

64
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:44,291
[Jin] Give me that.

65
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:47,083
I see.

66
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,375
It looks like a diary.

67
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:49,666
That's her diary?

68
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,916
Jackpot.

69
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,250
There' gotta be
some information

70
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,708
about that sunflower dude
in there somewhere.

71
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,875
Yeah.

72
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:59,375
Go on, read it to me, you mook.

73
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:02,250
The tenth of July, sunny-

74
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:05,166
<i>[Fuu] It's been almost</i>
<i>a year now, since Mom died.</i>

75
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:06,958
<i>I had always told</i>
<i>myself that one day</i>

76
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:09,125
<i>I would set out on a journey,</i>

77
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:11,541
<i>only I never had the courage,</i>
<i>so in the meantime,</i>

78
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:15,583
<i>I've been working and living</i>
<i>at this nice old guy's teahouse.</i>

79
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,166
<i>But now I've decided it's time.</i>

80
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:19,583
<i>I don't want</i>
<i>to forget this journey,</i>

81
00:04:19,666 --> 00:04:21,500
<i>and so I decided</i>
<i>that starting today,</i>

82
00:04:21,583 --> 00:04:23,000
<i>I'm going to keep this diary,</i>

83
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:26,666
<i>until I find the samurai</i>
<i>who smells of sunflowers.</i>

84
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:30,166
<i>And there you have it! I've kept</i>
<i>my word and started my diary.</i>

85
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,916
<i>I have now filled out</i>
<i>the very first page.</i>

86
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:37,250
<i>I have to admit that</i>
<i>the teahouse burning down</i>

87
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,750
<i>helped motivate me,</i>

88
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,583
<i>because I didn't have any choice</i>
<i>but to start my trip.</i>

89
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:43,833
<i>Parenthesis smiley face.</i>

90
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:46,083
<i>And as weird as this may</i>
<i>sound, the fire was caused</i>

91
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:48,500
<i>by a couple of crazy guys.</i>

92
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:53,666
<i>The first one to</i>
<i>come into the teahouse</i>

93
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:56,541
<i>was a crude and vulgar</i>
<i>guy with wild hair.</i>

94
00:04:56,625 --> 00:04:58,000
[Mugen] She talkin' about me?

95
00:04:58,083 --> 00:05:00,666
<i>The second I saw him,</i>
<i>I thought he was a bad guy,</i>

96
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:02,708
<i>the kind who commits</i>
<i>all sorts of crimes,</i>

97
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:04,750
<i>the type of person I'd</i>
<i>never want to be friends with</i>

98
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:05,791
<i>in a million years.</i>

99
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:07,208
[Mugen] Say what?

100
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,166
<i>Of course, once I</i>
<i>talked to him--</i>

101
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:10,333
[Mugen] Hmm?

102
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:11,625
<i>--I realized I was</i>
<i>absolutely right.</i>

103
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:13,333
[Mugen] Shut up
you little bitch.

104
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:14,625
[Jin] You're shouting
at a diary.

105
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,583
<i>I'll admit that</i>
<i>I needed some help.</i>

106
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:18,000
<i>The stupid</i>
<i>governor's son had come in</i>

107
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:20,458
<i>and thought he could</i>
<i>do whatever he wanted.</i>

108
00:05:20,541 --> 00:05:22,916
<i>But even so...</i>

109
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,333
[tape fast-forwarding]

110
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:26,375
<i>Once he got started,</i>
<i>he didn't know when to stop.</i>

111
00:05:26,458 --> 00:05:28,416
<i>I mean, he totally</i>
<i>went overboard.</i>

112
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,041
<i>If I'd known he was</i>
<i>going to do that,</i>

113
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:32,416
<i>I'd have taken my chances</i>
<i>with the governor's son.</i>

114
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,541
[Mugen] Why you little-

115
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,833
<i>In the middle of all this,</i>
<i>another man appeared,</i>

116
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,958
<i>one with long hair and glasses.</i>

117
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:40,625
[Mugen] She talkin'
'bout you now?

118
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:42,708
<i>I actually thought he</i>
<i>was kind of attractive,</i>

119
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,125
<i>not like the first one.</i>

120
00:05:44,208 --> 00:05:45,416
[Mugen] Huh?

121
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,583
[tape fast-forwarding]

122
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:48,291
<i>But once the new guy</i>
<i>got into it,</i>

123
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:50,291
<i>he refused to stop</i>
<i>fighting, too.</i>

124
00:05:50,375 --> 00:05:52,625
<i>they don't seem at all alike,</i>
<i>but maybe deep down</i>

125
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:54,333
<i>they're two of a kind.</i>

126
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:56,250
[Jin] How rude,
don't compare me--

127
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:58,750
[Mugen] --to a guy like him.

128
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:01,458
<i>Anyway, one thing led to</i>
<i>another, and before I knew it,</i>

129
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:04,083
<i>I had set out on my journey</i>
<i>with these two attendants:</i>

130
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,458
<i>Mugen and Jin.</i>

131
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:06,375
<i>The end.</i>

132
00:06:06,458 --> 00:06:07,541
[rewinding]

133
00:06:07,625 --> 00:06:10,083
<i>July the eleventh, sunny-</i>

134
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:11,791
<i>Something lousy</i>
<i>happened because of</i>

135
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:14,666
<i>those two going</i>
<i>crazy yesterday.</i>

136
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:18,125
<i>A guy showed up saying something</i>
<i>about Mugen cutting his arm off.</i>

137
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,208
Hey there.

138
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:20,541
[gasping]

139
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:24,416
I think you should
go back to sleep for a while.

140
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:25,916
[Fuu grunting]

141
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,291
<i>And so all of a sudden,</i>
<i>I'm this guy's hostage, geez.</i>

142
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:31,041
<i>Well, I was a little</i>
<i>drunk at the time,</i>

143
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:32,875
<i>so I don't remember too much.</i>

144
00:06:32,958 --> 00:06:34,083
<i>The end.</i>

145
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:35,625
That's it? The end?

146
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:37,125
Very brief.

147
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:40,875
<i>P.S. The aki manjuu we had</i>
<i>in Joshuu were yummy.</i>

148
00:06:40,958 --> 00:06:42,458
[rewinding]

149
00:06:42,541 --> 00:06:45,708
<i>July 14th, sunny then cloudy-</i>

150
00:06:45,791 --> 00:06:48,708
<i>I had another rotten day today</i>
<i>because of those two.</i>

151
00:06:48,791 --> 00:06:52,291
<i>It all started when they</i>
<i>ditched me and ran away.</i>

152
00:06:52,375 --> 00:06:55,833
<i>Thanks to that, I ended up</i>
<i>in a whorehouse this time.</i>

153
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:58,166
<i>A pervert was about</i>
<i>to have his way with me,</i>

154
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,250
<i>but thanks to an old</i>
<i>fortuneteller's advice,</i>

155
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,291
<i>I was saved.</i>

156
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:02,375
[rewinding]

157
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:05,708
I would beware of vases
if I were you.

158
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:06,875
[ceramic breaking]

159
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:07,916
Vase?

160
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,791
[screaming]

161
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:10,833
A vase. It's like a little vase.

162
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:13,166
Go away!

163
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:14,500
[ceramic breaking]

164
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:18,458
<i>July 19th-</i>

165
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:22,208
<i>Out of the blue, I was</i>
<i>kidnapped and held prisoner.</i>

166
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:23,666
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

167
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:26,666
<i>Don't you think my life</i>
<i>is a little too eventful?</i>

168
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:29,041
<i>You know, I have to</i>
<i>wonder sometimes...</i>

169
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:30,750
<i>Why do these things</i>
<i>keep happening to me,</i>

170
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:33,083
<i>even though I have</i>
<i>two bodyguards?</i>

171
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:36,583
<i>Those bozos are pretty useless</i>
<i>for the most part.</i>

172
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,166
<i>I'm really starting</i>
<i>to think that I may have</i>

173
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,791
<i>picked the wrong guys.</i>

174
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:43,166
<i>I first realized this</i>
<i>when we had to earn money</i>

175
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:45,125
<i>for the ferry boat</i>
<i>to cross the river.</i>

176
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:46,541
[rewinding]

177
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:49,000
My name's Moronobu Hishikawa,

178
00:07:49,083 --> 00:07:51,250
and I'm a struggling
young artist.

179
00:07:53,083 --> 00:07:55,000
Pleased to meet you.

180
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:58,250
<i>I thought he was kinda cute,</i>
<i>even if he was a bit of a poser.</i>

181
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,500
<i>Maybe that's where</i>
<i>I made my mistake.</i>

182
00:08:00,583 --> 00:08:02,958
<i>I went ahead and modeled</i>
<i>for his ukiyo-e painting,</i>

183
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,666
<i>but now that I think</i>
<i>about it, I don't know</i>

184
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:07,000
<i>what I ever saw in that guy.</i>

185
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,541
<i>Still, he did say</i>
<i>nice things to me,</i>

186
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:15,500
<i>which is more than I can say</i>
<i>for those two jerks.</i>

187
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:18,833
<i>Yeah, that mess was definitely</i>
<i>all their fault, too.</i>

188
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:21,416
[Mugen] Hey, don't blame
your screw-ups on us.

189
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,333
<i>He said that he was going to get</i>
<i>on a ship and go to Holland,</i>

190
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:26,666
<i>but I wonder what ever</i>
<i>happened to him.</i>

191
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,041
<i>I wonder if he's</i>
<i>on that ship right now.</i>

192
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:33,416
<i>Or who knows, maybe he's even</i>
<i>arrived there already.</i>

193
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:34,666
[rewinding]

194
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,166
<i>[Manzo] He, meaning</i>
<i>Moronobu Hishikawa,</i>

195
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,958
<i>was caught even before</i>
<i>he had a chance to leave port,</i>

196
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:42,041
<i>and never made it to Holland.</i>

197
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:45,208
<i>The fact is, he still</i>
<i>resides in that area.</i>

198
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:47,958
<i>However, there was no way</i>
<i>she could have known that</i>

199
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:49,666
<i>the man she met that day</i>

200
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,833
<i>would be recognized</i>
<i>by future generations</i>

201
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:54,666
<i>as the father of</i>
<i>ukiyo-e painting</i>

202
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:57,458
<i>In this world of ours,</i>
<i>talent and character are often</i>

203
00:08:57,541 --> 00:09:00,458
<i>discovered in</i>
<i>inverse proportions.</i>

204
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:03,333
<i>[Fuu] P.S. The fried</i>
<i>squid he treated us to</i>

205
00:09:03,416 --> 00:09:05,875
<i>was totally delicious.</i>

206
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:08,583
Somethin' just occurred to me
that I didn't think of before.

207
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:10,083
Like what?

208
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:12,500
Like what the hell were we
even doin' going to Edo anyway?

209
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:13,625
No idea.

210
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:17,125
Take a look already,
what'd she write?

211
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:20,708
<i>Today was the first time in ages</i>
<i>I was able to eat all I wanted.</i>

212
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,333
<i>I'm so happy.</i>

213
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:24,625
<i>I figured I might have to go</i>
<i>without food again after this,</i>

214
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:26,833
<i>so I ate enough</i>
<i>to tide me over.</i>

215
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,291
Is she an animal?

216
00:09:28,375 --> 00:09:30,583
<i>Some of the items on</i>
<i>yesterday's menu included</i>

217
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:34,708
<i>eel rice bowls, loach stew,</i>
<i>and Edo-style sushi.</i>

218
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:36,416
<i>They were all yummy.</i>

219
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,625
<i>You hear lots of people say,</i>

220
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:39,208
<i>"There's always</i>
<i>room for dessert,"</i>

221
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,958
<i>but in my case, I think it</i>
<i>should be something more like,</i>

222
00:09:42,041 --> 00:09:44,250
<i>"There's always room</i>
<i>for free food."</i>

223
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,083
<i>I wonder if</i>
<i>everybody's like that?</i>

224
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:47,583
[Mugen] Just you, Porky.

225
00:09:47,666 --> 00:09:48,833
[Jin] Mmm.

226
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:51,125
<i>I also got to see</i>
<i>kabuki and fireworks,</i>

227
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,291
<i>which was really neat.</i>

228
00:09:52,375 --> 00:09:53,625
<i>The end.</i>

229
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:55,666
Come on, wait a minute.
Isn't there anything about

230
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,625
that sunflower
samurai in there?

231
00:09:57,708 --> 00:09:59,000
Hmm.

232
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:01,416
All that she's writin' about
so far about is food.

233
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,875
<i>Oh, that reminds me,</i>

234
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:05,666
<i>we're leaving today</i>
<i>and going to Nagasaki.</i>

235
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:07,541
<i>I pretty much figure</i>
<i>it's a long shot,</i>

236
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:09,708
<i>but the reason I came to Edo</i>
<i>was because I'd heard rumors</i>

237
00:10:09,791 --> 00:10:11,166
<i>that he was here.</i>

238
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,833
<i>It's not like I had any</i>
<i>hard evidence or anything.</i>

239
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:15,250
You're kidding me.

240
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,541
[Mugen] That little Bitch.

241
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,333
She dragged us there
because of a stupid rumor?

242
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,083
I can't believe it.

243
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:29,625
<i>I got taken</i>
<i>hostage again, geez.</i>

244
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:31,458
<i>Is there anyone in the</i>
<i>whole world who's been</i>

245
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:33,458
<i>taken hostage as much as me?</i>

246
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:35,708
<i>To top it off,</i>
<i>my wallet got stolen,</i>

247
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:38,208
<i>and I couldn't buy</i>
<i>anything to eat.</i>

248
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,791
<i>I dreamed about</i>
<i>mom last night.</i>

249
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:47,791
<i>It was the first time</i>
<i>that I thought about her</i>

250
00:10:47,875 --> 00:10:49,333
<i>in a long time.</i>

251
00:10:51,125 --> 00:10:52,666
<i>It seems strange, I know.</i>

252
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,416
<i>But so much has happened</i>
<i>to me on this journey</i>

253
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,750
<i>that I haven't had any</i>
<i>time to miss her.</i>

254
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:59,625
<i>So, I haven't felt this way</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

255
00:11:01,291 --> 00:11:03,000
<i>It's hard for me to</i>
<i>find the right words</i>

256
00:11:03,083 --> 00:11:05,000
<i>to write about Shinsuke.</i>

257
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:06,666
<i>I just couldn't</i>
<i>bring myself to say</i>

258
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:08,833
<i>anything to his mother, either.</i>

259
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:12,416
<i>But once some time has passed,</i>

260
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,625
<i>and I've had a chance</i>
<i>to sort out my feelings,</i>

261
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:18,291
<i>I definitely want to sit down</i>
<i>and write her a long letter.</i>

262
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:19,666
<i>I want to tell her</i>
<i>all those things</i>

263
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:23,250
<i>that I wanted to say back</i>
<i>then, but couldn't.</i>

264
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:27,458
<i>[Manzo] It is difficult,</i>
<i>if not impossible</i>

265
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:30,375
<i>for anyone to predict</i>
<i>what the future holds.</i>

266
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:32,791
<i>Incidentally, this is</i>
<i>a prediction of the lives</i>

267
00:11:32,875 --> 00:11:34,291
<i>of people in the future,</i>

268
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:37,208
<i>taken from "Mudaiki,"</i>
<i>a speculative work of fiction</i>

269
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:40,625
<i>by Edo dime novel author</i>
<i>Harumachi Koikawa.</i>

270
00:11:40,708 --> 00:11:42,916
<i>As you can see here,</i>
<i>predicting the future</i>

271
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,083
<i>is something of</i>
<i>a tricky business.</i>

272
00:11:45,166 --> 00:11:47,666
<i>A case in point, what the</i>
<i>hell were they thinking</i>

273
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:50,625
<i>with those dumbass hairstyles?</i>

274
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:52,125
[rewinding]

275
00:11:52,208 --> 00:11:55,166
<i>[Fuu] We left Edo and</i>
<i>started out for Nagasaki.</i>

276
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:57,916
<i>Well, we tried to,</i>
<i>but we're still in Edo.</i>

277
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,791
<i>We can't make any headway at</i>
<i>all, 'cause we've got no money.</i>

278
00:12:01,875 --> 00:12:03,375
<i>At least we managed</i>
<i>to get a meal,</i>

279
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:06,625
<i>thanks to the money we got</i>
<i>when we pawned Jin's glasses.</i>

280
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:08,416
<i>It was yummy.</i>

281
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,416
<i>But then, those two went</i>
<i>crawling away</i>

282
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:12,333
<i>after some older woman.</i>

283
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:14,125
<i>What scumbags.</i>

284
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:15,291
<i>Hey, don't get me wrong,</i>

285
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:17,500
<i>it's not like</i>
<i>I'm jealous or anything.</i>

286
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,416
<i>It's just that it makes</i>
<i>things a lot more difficult</i>

287
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,708
<i>when my bodyguards</i>
<i>don't carry out their duties.</i>

288
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,708
<i>Well, I guess</i>
<i>she was kinda sexy.</i>

289
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:28,208
<i>She did have</i>
<i>a nice set of hooters.</i>

290
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:31,041
<i>Is that the kinda</i>
<i>women they go for?</i>

291
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,500
<i>Aww, who cares.</i>

292
00:12:32,583 --> 00:12:34,583
<i>I got hit on today, too.</i>

293
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:38,625
<i>Although admittedly the guy</i>
<i>didn't make a whole lotta sense.</i>

294
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:39,958
[rewinding]

295
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,708
It takes time to crack a pearl.

296
00:12:41,791 --> 00:12:45,875
That's alright, it just makes
that jewel a lot more desirable.

297
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:48,083
Hi there, Honey. Who am I?

298
00:12:48,166 --> 00:12:54,291
I'm gonna be big. My name is...
Nagamitsu Sakon Shogen.

299
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:56,125
<i>[sighing] I'm starting</i>
<i>to get the feeling that</i>

300
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:59,708
<i>I only attract weirdoes.</i>
<i>What's a girl to do?</i>

301
00:12:59,791 --> 00:13:01,250
<i>In the end,</i>
<i>we picked up a little money</i>

302
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,291
<i>with a street performance,</i>

303
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:04,416
<i>and we were</i>
<i>able to leave Edo.</i>

304
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,083
<i>But with every passing day,</i>

305
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:09,541
<i>it feels like I'm losing sight</i>
<i>of what I'm really after.</i>

306
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:11,000
<i>We're supposed</i>
<i>to be looking for</i>

307
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:13,166
<i>the samurai who</i>
<i>smells of sunflowers.</i>

308
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,791
<i>But we always end up</i>
<i>spending all our time</i>

309
00:13:14,875 --> 00:13:17,625
<i>scrounging up enough</i>
<i>money to survive.</i>

310
00:13:17,708 --> 00:13:19,875
<i>I guess the point</i>
<i>I'm trying to make here is:</i>

311
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:22,416
<i>getting by in life sure is hard.</i>

312
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:23,750
<i>The end.</i>

313
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:26,500
<i>P.S. the pear was yummy.</i>

314
00:13:26,583 --> 00:13:27,958
[rewinding]

315
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:30,083
<i>[Manzo] As a side note,</i>
<i>there's been a recent uproar</i>

316
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:33,166
<i>over rampant sexuality</i>
<i>in the country's youth.</i>

317
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,541
<i>However, keep in mind</i>
<i>that Japanese people</i>

318
00:13:35,625 --> 00:13:38,375
<i>had a rather open-minded</i>
<i>view of sexuality,</i>

319
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:41,291
<i>And it was especially liberal</i>
<i>during the Edo Period.</i>

320
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:43,750
<i>They only became prudish</i>
<i>in the Meiji Era</i>

321
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,583
<i>after the influx of</i>
<i>Western culture.</i>

322
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:48,291
<i>So, to put this in perspective,</i>

323
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:49,791
<i>one could say</i>
<i>that they've merely</i>

324
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:52,583
<i>returned to the values</i>
<i>of the Edo Period.</i>

325
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:55,666
<i>And if you take the time</i>
<i>to delve into world history,</i>

326
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,708
<i>then you'll discover that</i>
<i>Japan's Edo Period can be placed</i>

327
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:01,833
<i>right alongside the civilization</i>
<i>of ancient Greece,</i>

328
00:14:01,916 --> 00:14:04,583
<i>and that it was an era in</i>
<i>which gay love flourished,</i>

329
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:07,708
<i>and homosexuality was considered</i>
<i>a more noble pursuit</i>

330
00:14:07,791 --> 00:14:09,458
<i>than heterosexuality.</i>

331
00:14:09,541 --> 00:14:13,291
<i>Incidentally, please forgive my</i>
<i>extremely delayed introduction.</i>

332
00:14:13,375 --> 00:14:15,750
<i>My name is Manzo the Saw.</i>

333
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,791
<i>I'm an officer with</i>
<i>the secret police,</i>

334
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:21,375
<i>and I fight night and day</i>
<i>in the name of peace.</i>

335
00:14:21,458 --> 00:14:22,500
[rewinding]

336
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,916
<i>[Fuu] I got</i>
<i>taken prisoner again.</i>

337
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,000
<i>We finally left Edo and got as</i>
<i>far as the Kanto checkpoint,</i>

338
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:31,250
<i>when we got conned by a scalper.</i>

339
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:33,416
<i>It seems like I've been</i>
<i>scammed a lot</i>

340
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,375
<i>since I started</i>
<i>on this journey.</i>

341
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,791
<i>I don't know, am I too naïve?</i>

342
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:40,833
<i>Maybe I ought to be</i>
<i>more suspicious of people.</i>

343
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:43,458
<i>Am I a bad judge of character?</i>

344
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,875
<i>I had a lot</i>
<i>to think about today.</i>

345
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:49,083
<i>Of course the worst part of it</i>
<i>all is that jerk, Mugen.</i>

346
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:52,000
<i>I believed in him,</i>
<i>thinking he'd come back for us.</i>

347
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:55,333
<i>What kind of rescuer</i>
<i>ends up needing to be rescued?</i>

348
00:14:55,416 --> 00:14:58,333
<i>Anyway, I finally decided</i>
<i>never to trust him again.</i>

349
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,208
[Mugen] Yeah, well that
suits me just fine.

350
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:03,333
Go ahead and don't trust me.
See if I care.

351
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:05,833
<i>By the way, I spent</i>
<i>a lot of time with Jin,</i>

352
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:08,583
<i>because that jerk,</i>
<i>Mugen, didn't come back.</i>

353
00:15:08,666 --> 00:15:10,125
<i>Now that I think about it,</i>

354
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:12,208
<i>I guess that was</i>
<i>the first time I ever</i>

355
00:15:12,291 --> 00:15:13,666
<i>spent any time alone with him.</i>

356
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:15,333
[Mugen] Huh?

357
00:15:15,416 --> 00:15:17,708
<i>I thought to myself,</i>
<i>"We're finally going to have</i>

358
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,875
<i>a heart to heart conversation."</i>

359
00:15:19,958 --> 00:15:22,000
<i>But Jin kept his mouth</i>
<i>shut the whole time.</i>

360
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:24,375
<i>It was like he'd</i>
<i>taken a vow of silence.</i>

361
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:26,125
<i>I'd always thought that</i>
<i>at times like that,</i>

362
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:29,291
<i>guys were supposed to open up</i>
<i>and tell you all sorts of stuff.</i>

363
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,666
<i>I tried to break the ice, but</i>
<i>all I could get out of him was</i>

364
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:34,416
<i>a "Hmm," or an "Aah."</i>

365
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,333
<i>What's his problem?</i>
<i>That's what I'd like to know.</i>

366
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:38,125
<i>Does he hate me or something?</i>

367
00:15:38,208 --> 00:15:40,875
<i>Or is he just shy?</i>

368
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:42,625
<i>I mean, after all,</i>
<i>we've been on this journey</i>

369
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:44,166
<i>for quite a while now.</i>

370
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:46,083
<i>How long is it going</i>
<i>to take before</i>

371
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:48,125
<i>he finally gets around</i>
<i>to opening up to me?</i>

372
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,041
<i>It's kinda sad, really.</i>

373
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:52,166
<i>The end.</i>

374
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:55,416
Jin, man-to-man, what do you
really think of her, anyway?

375
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,500
Hmm.

376
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:58,833
[sighing] This guy's hopeless.

377
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,416
[rewinding]

378
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:04,458
<i>[Manzo] The 1950s,</i>
<i>San Francisco, California.</i>

379
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:07,500
<i>A time in which the youth of</i>
<i>the so-called Beat Generation</i>

380
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:10,791
<i>were profoundly</i>
<i>influenced by Zen.</i>

381
00:16:10,875 --> 00:16:12,791
<i>And that influence, in turn,</i>

382
00:16:12,875 --> 00:16:16,166
<i>was passed on to</i>
<i>the Hippies of the 1960s.</i>

383
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,333
<i>Also known as</i>
<i>the flower children,</i>

384
00:16:18,416 --> 00:16:20,833
<i>they turned away</i>
