386
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,916
<i>and searched for true freedom.</i>

387
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,291
<i>It is said that among the</i>
<i>Hippies, there were those</i>

388
00:16:28,375 --> 00:16:30,875
<i>who approached Zen</i>
<i>as a counterculture,</i>

389
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:33,791
<i>chanted Buddhist mantras,</i>
<i>burned incense,</i>

390
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,041
<i>and practiced meditation.</i>

391
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:39,625
<i>Elsewhere, during</i>
<i>the Edo Period in Japan,</i>

392
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:42,958
<i>although they aren't searching</i>
<i>for anything in particular,</i>

393
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:46,416
<i>here we find three people</i>
<i>deep in meditation.</i>

394
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:51,750
<i>And if one were to ask why these</i>
<i>people are doing this, well...</i>

395
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:59,625
I'm sorry, friend, but we
don't even have enough money

396
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:01,208
for a place to sleep.

397
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:03,833
We don't have anything
to give you for charity.

398
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:06,666
[Zuikou] Well, that's wonderful.
I'm glad to hear that.

399
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,041
Huh?

400
00:17:09,875 --> 00:17:12,166
<i>[Fuu] Starting today, we'll be</i>
<i>staying at this Zen temple</i>

401
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,500
<i>for a while.</i>

402
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:15,166
<i>The monk in charge of</i>
<i>the temple is giving us</i>

403
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:17,291
<i>free room and board</i>
<i>while we're here.</i>

404
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:19,166
<i>It's more than</i>
<i>we could have hoped for.</i>

405
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:23,166
<i>But in return, we have to follow</i>
<i>the strict rules of the temple.</i>

406
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:26,666
<i>I've been working hard since</i>
<i>the crack of dawn again today.</i>

407
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,375
<i>Boy am I beat.</i>

408
00:17:29,875 --> 00:17:30,958
Since the beginning,

409
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,791
man was born into
a state of freedom.

410
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:37,625
He was not born so that he might
submit to rules or to a master.

411
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,458
This thought has occurred to me.

412
00:17:39,541 --> 00:17:40,958
My question is this: 

413
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:43,541
the duties of a warrior...
Does this philosophy

414
00:17:43,625 --> 00:17:45,791
not contradict them?

415
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:49,625
No, because freedom cannot
be forced into existence.

416
00:17:49,708 --> 00:17:52,208
Nor can it be won
through painful struggle.

417
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:54,791
