be bought or sold.

418
00:17:54,875 --> 00:17:57,583
It has nothing to do
with one's social status.

419
00:17:57,666 --> 00:18:01,000
One's profession
is of no consequence.

420
00:18:01,083 --> 00:18:03,125
In order for you
to accept yourself as you are

421
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:05,250
and live with
your soul at peace,

422
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:08,083
you must simply
teach yourself to let it be.

423
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:11,250
Only then will you
discover freedom.

424
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,208
Those idiots.

425
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:15,916
A lot of terrible things
happened to me lately,

426
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,083
and it's all because of them.

427
00:18:18,166 --> 00:18:20,500
I have to wonder at times.

428
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:23,375
Did I pick the right two men
to go with me on this journey?

429
00:18:23,458 --> 00:18:24,791
Ya know?

430
00:18:24,875 --> 00:18:27,958
[Zuikou] All encounters happen
but once in a lifetime.

431
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,916
There is no right or wrong.

432
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,250
If you have met these two men
and are traveling with them now,

433
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:37,416
then that is your destiny.
For better or worse,

434
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,625
whatever the outcome
of your journey may be.

435
00:18:41,958 --> 00:18:43,583
[Mugen] Hey, Master Chrome Dome,

436
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:45,541
I'm lookin' to
make myself stronger, here.

437
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:48,500
You got any brilliant ideas?

438
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:50,958
I wanna beat
that freaky bastard.

439
00:18:51,041 --> 00:18:53,083
Hey, you listenin' to me, baldy?

440
00:18:53,166 --> 00:18:55,833
How the hell am I
supposed to beat this guy?

441
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:58,375
Come on!
Start talkin', cue ball.

442
00:18:59,541 --> 00:18:59,958
[Zuikou] Katsu!

443
00:19:00,041 --> 00:19:01,166
Ow!

444
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:07,625
Look at that moon,
it's so big tonight.

445
00:19:07,708 --> 00:19:09,416
[Mugen] I'm headin' out
for a bit.

446
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,916
You haven't forgotten
your promise, have you?

447
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,416
Huh?

448
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:16,291
The samurai who smells
of sunflowers, remember?

449
00:19:16,375 --> 00:19:18,666
Don't forget, you said
you'd help me find him.

450
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:21,541
I won't forget.

451
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:22,500
[Jin] One other thing.

452
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:23,666
Hmm?

453
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:26,166
I shall be the one
who gets to slay you.

454
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,250
<i>[Fuu] Looking back now,</i>
<i>sure a lot</i>

455
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:30,875
<i>of crappy stuff has happened,</i>

456
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:33,958
<i>but I've experienced</i>
<i>all sorts of new things, too.</i>

457
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:37,333
<i>If Mugen and Jin hadn't wandered</i>
<i>into the teahouse that day,</i>

458
00:19:37,416 --> 00:19:40,583
<i>then chances are, I'd still</i>
<i>be working there right now.</i>

459
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:42,208
<i>When I think of it that way,</i>

460
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:44,875
<i>maybe it's like</i>
<i>Father Zuikou says:</i>

461
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:47,666
<i>It was a once in a</i>
<i>lifetime chance encounter.</i>

462
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:51,125
<i>I have no idea what stands</i>
<i>between here and Nagasaki</i>

463
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:53,541
<i>or how much longer</i>
<i>it'll take us to get there.</i>

464
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:55,375
<i>I just hope</i>
<i>the three of us can keep</i>

465
00:19:55,458 --> 00:19:58,000
<i>traveling together</i>
<i>to the very end.</i>

466
00:19:58,083 --> 00:20:01,791
<i>I'm positive that those two are</i>
<i>thinking the exact same thing.</i>

467
00:20:01,875 --> 00:20:04,500
<i>Yep, that's the path</i>
<i>I chose to take.</i>

468
00:20:06,041 --> 00:20:08,583
[Mugen] You don't make up
other people's minds for them.

469
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:09,375
Right?

470
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:10,541
[Jin] Hmm.

471
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:11,833
<i>[Fuu] Just kidding.</i>

472
00:20:11,916 --> 00:20:13,416
<i>I figured those two</i>
<i>might try and get a peek</i>

473
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,250
<i>at my diary without asking,</i>

474
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,500
<i>so I decided to make</i>
<i>all that stuff up.</i>

475
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:20,958
<i>Serves you right, you jerks.</i>

476
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,833
You--

477
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:25,791
[Mugen screaming]
--you little bitch!

478
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:32,708
<i>♪ End Theme ♪</i>

